FOURTH OF JULY LOVE-IN'

On the Fourth we will not celebrate America's Independence we will celebrate LOVE. In honor of LOVE I am hosting a LOVE-IN' at my house. You MUST be lovely. You MUST love (or pretend to love). 
We will celebrate Friendship LOVE. Love LOVE. LOVE for humanity. LOVE for all things.
We'll start around 7 ish. 
Bring friends and lovers.
And because I will be at this Love-In' there will be 40s. Bring booze to share, or not. Bring what you love. 
Bring food. Chips of LOVE. Cupcakes of LOVE. Fondue of LOVE.
Bring bring bring.
Bring lovely music. 
Bring yourself. 
Come to my LOVE-IN'!!!
<3

6436 Catina
New Orleans 70124

MapQuest it!!

NOTE: I, lovely Meg, throw lovely parties. Every lovely person should come.

Party at Grant's house! Everyone is invited even if you don't know Grant. Saturday-Monday afternoon.
Come on over and enjoy delicious bbq, drinks, music, etc. 
Lots of fun. Be there. 
Call me for further information. 504-577-0169

Birthday gift number one:

http://www.eluxury.com/browse/product_detail.jhtml?styleid=10392976&SectionID=6000

Aaaaw Yeah! It came with the little super soft storage bag and the official LV tags and stuff. LOVE IT!

WHAT: My birthday party
WHEN: Friday night/Saturday morning at midnight.
WHERE: My house.
THEME: UNDER THE SEA PIZZA PARTY

You heard it. The party is officially on Friday night at midnight. Come dressed as your favorite sea creature if you wish (this is highly encouraged). Bring some soda or beer or whatever you drink and movies and sea themed snacks. We're going to watch movies and play pool  and chill and be awesome.  

Note: To have the party there's a "TEN SUPER HOTTIES" requirement by the roommates. That means you. You have to be there or I'll be kicked out of the house.

Call me or post a comment if you have any questions. 504-577-0169

<3

There's going to be a birthday party this weekend cause it's my birthday. Please reply with which day you prefer (Friday or Saturday). 
I'm thinking pizza party and movies and beer and  vodka and you and stuff. Yeah. 
Any suggestions? I'm totally open to suggestions. 
And we all know that in typical Meg fashion this will change one million times before the party so beware. 
You better come to my party. 
Call me. 504-577-0169.

I live in the lamest house ever. It's saturday night and we're all in our respective rooms either playing video games, watching tv or using the internet. We're awesome. Every once in a while Scott yells "FUCK" at his video game. And sometimes one of the cats comes upstairs to check us all out. The new roommate came over tonight. He moves in on Monday and he seems pretty chill. That's all I have to say.
chicken nachos are my new boyfriend.

06. I will tell you what animal you remind me of.

08. Put this in your journal

1. a movie
2. a book

Then put this in your LJ and I'll (try to) do the same for you.

You Are 23 Years Old
23
Under 12: You are a kid at heart. You still have an optimistic life view - and you look at the world with awe. 13-19: You are a teenager at heart. You question authority and are still trying to find your place in this world. 20-29: You are a twentysomething at heart. You feel excited about what's to come... love, work, and new experiences. 30-39: You are a thirtysomething at heart. You've had a taste of success and true love, but you want more! 40+: You are a mature adult. You've been through most of the ups and downs of life already. Now you get to sit back and relax.

You are an onion in a cup. But you knew that
already. You make people cry, but not on
purpose. You're honest. Hey, if you had bad
breath, you'd want someone to tell you. So you
do the same to them. As natural as the truth
feels, and as much as you hate liars, both of
those things might keep you a little bit
seperated form the rest of humanity. Very few
people understand the value of truth. That
distance, sometimes lonliness, is what you have
to live with when you're true to yourself.

The moral of the story...
DON'T PISS ME OFF!

Anyone up for some REAL food tonight? I'm tired of pizza and salad.

This hurricane evacuation business has turned into quite an adventure for me. It took 2 days to get to Austin, Tx, but it was totally worth it. Now, Lauren is on her way to meet me and we're going to spend the next day and a half at the Austin City Limits festival. Modest Mouse, The Pixies, Cat Power, Ben Harper, Elvis Costello, Ben Kweller, Franz Ferdinand...
No school until Monday.
I ate too much ice cream. I feel sick.

Lauren, the Baby, and I went to bubble tea this afternoon. Some old people thought that the baby was Lauren's. That was funny.
I think Daddy and I are going bike shopping tomorrow afternoon. I found one at a flea market in Slidell last Saturday. I hope it's still there. 
Tomorrow night is White Linen Night. I'm in the process of making a white linen skirt. Hopefully it will be done in time. 
Don't forget, the Mermaid Garden Flea Market is this Sunday. Also Glasgow will be playing at Rock N' Bowl on Sunday at 5:30 ( I think).

You know how it goes.
